        <mxCell id="78gB0I-AgeketshrQ1jP-154" parent="78gB0I-AgeketshrQ1jP-94" style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;darkOpacity=0.05;rounded=1;shadow=0;glass=0;labelBackgroundColor=none;sketch=0;strokeColor=#d6b656;strokeWidth=2;fontSize=23;fillColor=#CFE7FC;opacity=60;align=left;spacingTop=1;spacingLeft=20;spacingBottom=22;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;verticalAlign=top;arcSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=default;fontStyle=0;" value="&lt;b&gt;K8s &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;b&gt;Namespace&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span&gt;A &quot;namespace&quot; is a network boundary in Kubernetes&#39; pod networking, at the IP layer. It means that network requests from containers are only routed to pods/containers within the same namespace. A &#39;network policy&#39; can be defined to explicit allow requests between namespaces.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
